From: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
Subject: [PATCH] exit on device disconnect (NO_DEVICE) without relying on udev

usb-proxy only exits on disconnect via its libusb hotplug DEVICE_LEFT
callback (kill(0,SIGINT)). libusb hotplug does not fire on systems without
udev (this appliance uses mdev), so on unplug usb-proxy lingers and the host
keeps a stale gadget. The IN endpoint threads already detect the gone device
(LIBUSB_ERROR_NO_DEVICE); raise SIGINT there to run the same clean shutdown
and let init respawn us to re-proxy on replug.

Signed-off-by: usb-proxy appliance <usb-proxy@local>
---
--- a/proxy.cpp
+++ b/proxy.cpp
@@ -736,8 +736,13 @@
 						       data, length, USB_REQUEST_TIMEOUT);
 				if (rv == LIBUSB_ERROR_NO_DEVICE) {
 					delete[] data;
-					printf("EP%x(%s_%s): device likely reset, stopping thread\n",
+					printf("EP%x(%s_%s): device gone, stopping usb-proxy\n",
 						ep.bEndpointAddress, transfer_type.c_str(), dir.c_str());
+					/* libusb hotplug does not fire without udev; the device is
+					 * gone, so trigger the same clean shutdown the hotplug
+					 * callback would (SIGINT) and let the service manager
+					 * respawn us to re-proxy on replug. */
+					kill(0, SIGINT);
 					break;
 				}
 				if (rv != LIBUSB_SUCCESS)
@@ -747,8 +752,13 @@
